Adult male.description: Overlaps with Boat-tailed Grackle along the western Gulf Coast where Great-tailed Grackles have pale yellow eyes and Boat-tailed Grackles have dark eyes. Great-tailed Grackles are more likely to be seen away from coasts than Boat-tailed.

Female.description: Overlaps with Boat-tailed Grackle along the western Gulf Coast where Great-tailed Grackles have pale yellow eyes and Boat-tailed Grackles have dark eyes. Great-tailed Grackles are more likely to be seen away from coasts than Boat-tailed.

Adult male.description: Common Grackles are smaller with slimmer bills and shorter tails than Boat-tailed Grackles.

Female.description: Female and young Common Grackles are more uniformly dark brown than female Boat-tailed Grackle, and lack the subtle face pattern.

Adult/immature.description: Fish Crows are heavier and have larger bodies, thicker bills, and much shorter tails than Boat-tailed Grackles.
